org.jtransfo

Annotation Type PreConvert


  • @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Target(value={TYPE,ANNOTATION_TYPE})
 @Repeatable(value=PreConvert.List.class)
 @Documented
public @interface PreConvert
    Annotation to specify a PreConverter to be used when converting.

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Fields and Description
      static String DEFAULT_NAME
      Default value for value() indicating that converterClass() should be set.

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Class converterClass
      Class to use for preconvert.
      String value
      Name for the type converter, this is either name (when it implements Named or the Fully qualified class name.

    • Field Detail

      • DEFAULT_NAME

        public static final String DEFAULT_NAME
        Default value for value() indicating that converterClass() should be set.

    • Element Detail

      • value

        public abstract String value
        Name for the type converter, this is either name (when it implements Named or the Fully qualified class name.

        Using this allows you to avoid a compile dependency on the class name but makes the connection more brittle when refactoring. The value is ignored if converterClass() is set.

        Default:
        "?"

      • converterClass

        public abstract Class converterClass
        Class to use for preconvert.

        This requires a compile dependency on the domain class. The value has precedence over value().

        Default:
        org.jtransfo.PreConvert.class
